    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Settlements historically established by fugitive African slaves continue to serve as spaces of memory and resistance, preserving culture and tradition. The specific name they receive depends on the country. For instance, in Brazil, they are known as quilombos or mocambos, while in Venezuela, they are referred to as cumbes. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
